                                <strong><i class="ri-refresh-line" style="color:var(--ob-blue);margin-right:4px;"></i> Freshness vs. Scale</strong>
                                <p>Traditional vector DBs offer "eventual consistency" — stale RAG results. OceanBase guarantees strict ACID: queryable the millisecond data is written.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout">
                                <strong><i class="ri-code-s-slash-line" style="color:var(--ob-blue);margin-right:4px;"></i> Glue Code Tax</strong>
                                <p>Merging MySQL + ES + Vector DB results requires 500+ lines of Python. OceanBase does hybrid search in a single SQL query.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout">
                                <strong><i class="ri-tools-line" style="color:var(--ob-blue);margin-right:4px;"></i> Operational Fatigue</strong>
                                <p>Multiple clusters, multiple APIs, multiple failure modes — AI apps shouldn't be this complex.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <aside class="notes">Pain points: data silos, consistency, glue code, ops complexity. OceanBase solves all with one engine.</aside>
                    </section>
        
                    <!-- ══ Slide 3 · OceanBase Vector Capabilities ══ -->
                    <section data-background-color="#fafafa">
                        <div class="slide-label"><span class="pill">Capabilities</span></div>
                        <h2 class="slide-title">OceanBase Vector Capabilities</h2>
                        <div class="feature-grid" style="margin-top:1.2rem;">
                            <div class="feature-card">
                                <div class="feature-icon"><i class="ri-search-eye-line" style="color:var(--ob-blue);"></i></div>
                                <h4>Vector Storage &amp; Index</h4>
                                <p>VECTOR type + HNSW index, L2 / Inner Product / Cosine distance</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="feature-card">
                                <div class="feature-icon"><i class="ri-file-search-line" style="color:var(--ob-teal);"></i></div>
                                <h4>Full-Text Search</h4>
                                <p>Built-in FULLTEXT index, no Elasticsearch needed</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="feature-card">
                                <div class="feature-icon"><i class="ri-git-merge-line" style="color:var(--ob-blue);"></i></div>
                                <h4>Hybrid Search</h4>
                                <p>DBMS_HYBRID_SEARCH: vector + full-text + scalar filter in one query</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="feature-card">
                                <div class="feature-icon"><i class="ri-shield-check-line" style="color:var(--ob-teal);"></i></div>
                                <h4>ACID Transactions</h4>
                                <p>Scalar, vector, and full-text indexes update atomically — zero inconsistency window</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="feature-card">
                                <div class="feature-icon"><i class="ri-braces-line" style="color:var(--ob-blue);"></i></div>
                                <h4>JSON &amp; GIS</h4>
                                <p>Semi-structured and spatial data in one engine — full multi-modal coverage</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="feature-card">
                                <div class="feature-icon"><i class="ri-plug-line" style="color:var(--ob-teal);"></i></div>
                                <h4>MySQL Compatible</h4>
                                <p>Zero-rewrite migration for existing MySQL applications</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <aside class="notes">OceanBase V4.3.3+ natively supports vector types and HNSW indexes. Key advantage: one engine for everything.</aside>
                    </section>
        
                    <!-- ══ Slide 4 · pyobvector SDK ══ -->
                    <section data-background-color="#fafafa">
                        <div class="slide-label"><span class="pill">SDK</span></div>
                        <h2 class="slide-title">pyobvector — Two Python SDK Modes</h2>
                        <div class="grid-2" style="margin-top:1.2rem;">
                            <div class="callout">
                                <strong><i class="ri-api-line" style="color:var(--ob-blue);margin-right:4px;"></i> Milvus-Compatible Mode</strong>
                                <p>MilvusLikeClient class — API aligned with Milvus, zero-cost migration.</p>
                                <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:0.6rem;">
                                    <div class="code-block-title">Python</div>
                                    <pre><code class="language-python">from pyobvector import MilvusLikeClient
        
        client = MilvusLikeClient(
            uri="127.0.0.1:2881",
            user="root@test"
        )
        # Create collection + vector index
        client.create_collection(
            collection_name="docs",
            schema=schema,
            index_params=idx_params,
        )</code></pre>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout">
                                <strong><i class="ri-database-line" style="color:var(--ob-teal);margin-right:4px;"></i> SQLAlchemy Hybrid Mode</strong>
                                <p>ObVecClient class — vector ops + SQL queries in one, extends SQLAlchemy.</p>
                                <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:0.6rem;">
                                    <div class="code-block-title">Python</div>
                                    <pre><code class="language-python">from pyobvector import ObVecClient
        from sqlalchemy import func
        
        client = ObVecClient(
            uri="127.0.0.1:2881",
            user="root@test"
        )
        # ANN search + scalar filtering
        res = client.ann_search(
            table_name="docs",
            vec_data=embedding,
            vec_column_name="embedding",
            distance_func=func.l2_distance,
            topk=5,
        )</code></pre>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <aside class="notes">pyobvector offers two modes: Milvus-compatible (migration-friendly) and SQLAlchemy hybrid (flexible querying). Install: pip install pyobvector</aside>
                    </section>
        
                    <!-- ══ Slide 5 · LangChain Integration ══ -->
                    <section data-background-color="#fafafa">
                        <div class="slide-label"><span class="pill">Integration</span></div>
                        <h2 class="slide-title">langchain-oceanbase — LangChain VectorStore</h2>
                        <div class="step-list" style="margin-top:1rem;">
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <span class="step-num">01</span>
                                <div class="step-content">
                                    <strong>Install Dependencies</strong>
                                    <p><code>pip install langchain-oceanbase pyobvector</code></p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <span class="step-num">02</span>
                                <div class="step-content">
                                    <strong>Initialize OceanBaseVectorStore</strong>
                                    <p>Pass Embedding model + DB connection — auto-creates table and index</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <span class="step-num">03</span>
                                <div class="step-content">
                                    <strong>Add Documents</strong>
                                    <p><code>vectorstore.add_documents(docs)</code> — auto chunk, embed, store</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <span class="step-num">04</span>
                                <div class="step-content">
                                    <strong>Hybrid Retrieval</strong>
                                    <p>Vector similarity + full-text search + scalar filtering, configurable weight fusion</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:1rem;">
                            <div class="code-block-title">Python</div>
                            <pre><code class="language-python">from langchain_oceanbase import OceanBaseVectorStore
        from langchain_openai import OpenAIEmbeddings
        
        vs = OceanBaseVectorStore(
            embedding=OpenAIEmbeddings(),
            connection_args={
                "host": "127.0.0.1", "port": "2881",
                "user": "root@test", "password": "",
                "database": "test"
            },
        )
        
        # Add documents
        vs.add_documents(split_docs)
        
        # Hybrid search
        results = vs.similarity_search(
            "OceanBase distributed architecture", k=5
        )</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <aside class="notes">langchain-oceanbase v0.3.3 is on PyPI. Supports Hybrid Search and metadata filtering.</aside>
                    </section>
        
                    <!-- ══ Slide 6 · RAG Pipeline ══ -->
                    <section data-background-color="#fafafa">
                        <div class="slide-label"><span class="pill">RAG</span></div>
                        <h2 class="slide-title">End-to-End RAG Pipeline</h2>
                        <div class="grid-2" style="margin-top:1rem;">
                            <div class="callout">
                                <strong><i class="ri-file-text-line" style="color:var(--ob-blue);margin-right:4px;"></i> Document Ingestion</strong>
                                <p>LangChain DocumentLoader → TextSplitter → Embeddings → OceanBaseVectorStore</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout">
                                <strong><i class="ri-search-line" style="color:var(--ob-teal);margin-right:4px;"></i> Hybrid Retrieval</strong>
                                <p>User Query → Embedding → Vector + Full-text hybrid search → DBMS_HYBRID_SEARCH weighted fusion</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout">
                                <strong><i class="ri-robot-line" style="color:var(--ob-blue);margin-right:4px;"></i> Answer Generation</strong>
                                <p>Retriever → Context assembly → LLM (GPT-4 / Qwen / DeepSeek) → Structured output</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout">
                                <strong><i class="ri-loop-left-line" style="color:var(--ob-teal);margin-right:4px;"></i> Evaluation &amp; Iteration</strong>
                                <p>LangSmith / RAGAS evaluation → Tune chunk size, retrieval weights, reranker strategy</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:1rem;">
                            <div class="code-block-title">Python — RAG Chain</div>
                            <pre><code class="language-python">from langchain_core.output_parsers import StrOutputParser
        from langchain_core.runnables import RunnablePassthrough
        from langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI
        
        retriever = vs.as_retriever(search_kwargs={"k": 5})
        llm = ChatOpenAI(model="gpt-4o")
        
        rag_chain = (
            {"context": retriever | format_docs, "question": RunnablePassthrough()}
            | prompt
            | llm
            | StrOutputParser()
        )
        
        rag_chain.invoke("How does OceanBase achieve distributed consistency?")</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <aside class="notes">Full RAG pipeline: load docs → chunk → embed → store → retrieve → generate. OceanBase replaces Pinecone/Weaviate as VectorStore.</aside>
                    </section>
        
                    <!-- ══ Slide 7 · Hybrid Search Deep Dive ══ -->
                    <section data-background-color="#fafafa">
                        <div class="slide-label"><span class="pill">Hybrid Search</span></div>
                        <h2 class="slide-title">DBMS_HYBRID_SEARCH Deep Dive</h2>
                        <div class="step-list" style="margin-top:1rem;">
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <span class="step-num">01</span>
                                <div class="step-content">
                                    <strong>Scalar Filtering</strong>
                                    <p>WHERE clause narrows scope from millions to thousands</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <span class="step-num">02</span>
                                <div class="step-content">
                                    <strong>Coarse Ranking: Vector + Full-Text</strong>
                                    <p>HNSW vector ANN + FULLTEXT keyword match — low-cost parallel recall</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <span class="step-num">03</span>
                                <div class="step-content">
                                    <strong>Fine Ranking: Reranker</strong>
                                    <p>High-precision re-scoring with configurable vector/full-text weight ratio</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:1rem;">
                            <div class="code-block-title">SQL — Hybrid Search</div>
                            <pre><code class="language-sql">CALL DBMS_HYBRID_SEARCH(
          table_name   => 'knowledge_base',
          query_text   => 'distributed transaction consistency protocol',
          vector_col   => 'embedding',
          fulltext_col => 'content',
          top_k        => 10,
          alpha        => 0.7   -- vector weight 0.7, full-text weight 0.3
        );</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <aside class="notes">Alpha controls vector vs full-text weighting. 0.7 = 70% semantic + 30% keyword. Tune per use case.</aside>
                    </section>
        
                    <!-- ══ Slide 8 · Comparison Table ══ -->
                    <section data-background-color="#fafafa">
                        <div class="slide-label"><span class="pill">Comparison</span></div>
                        <h2 class="slide-title">Architecture Comparison: Why OceanBase?</h2>
                        <table style="margin-top:1rem;">
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th style="width:22%;">Feature</th>
                                    <th style="width:26%;">Classic Stack<br><small>SQL + ES + Vector DB</small></th>
                                    <th style="width:26%;">Specialist Stack<br><small>SQL + Pinecone</small></th>
                                    <th style="width:26%;background:var(--ob-blue-10);">OceanBase<br><small>Unified Engine</small></th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><strong>Systems</strong></td>
                                    <td>3</td>
                                    <td>2</td>
                                    <td style="background:var(--ob-blue-10);"><strong>1</strong></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><strong>Data Consistency</strong></td>
                                    <td>Weak / Eventual</td>
                                    <td>No TX guarantee</td>
                                    <td style="background:var(--ob-blue-10);"><strong>Strict ACID</strong></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><strong>Search</strong></td>
                                    <td>Strong FT, weak vector</td>
                                    <td>Strong vector, weak FT</td>
                                    <td style="background:var(--ob-blue-10);"><strong>Vector + FT + Scalar</strong></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><strong>Dev Experience</strong></td>
                                    <td>3x ops + sync debugging</td>
                                    <td>Heavy glue code</td>
                                    <td style="background:var(--ob-blue-10);"><strong>SQL-native, zero glue</strong></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><strong>MySQL Compat</strong></td>
                                    <td>Partial</td>
                                    <td>No</td>
                                    <td style="background:var(--ob-blue-10);"><strong>Full</strong></td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                        <aside class="notes">Key selling point: one engine replaces three systems, strict ACID, SQL-native hybrid search.</aside>
                    </section>
        
                    <!-- ══ Slide 9 · Quick Start ══ -->
                    <section data-background-color="#fafafa">
                        <div class="slide-label"><span class="pill">Quick Start</span></div>
                        <h2 class="slide-title">Up and Running in 5 Minutes</h2>
                        <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:1rem;">
                            <div class="code-block-title">Shell — Docker Launch</div>
                            <pre><code class="language-bash"># Start OceanBase CE (vector support requires V4.3.3+)
        docker run -d --name ob \
          -p 2881:2881 \
          -e OB_MEMORY_LIMIT=6G \
          oceanbase/oceanbase-ce:4.3.5-lts</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:0.6rem;">
                            <div class="code-block-title">Shell — Install &amp; Run</div>
                            <pre><code class="language-bash">pip install langchain-oceanbase pyobvector langchain-openai
        
        # Or use seekdb lightweight edition
        docker run -d --name seekdb \
          -p 2881:2881 -p 2886:2886 \
          -v ./seekdb:/var/lib/oceanbase \
          oceanbase/seekdb:latest</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:0.6rem;">
                            <div class="code-block-title">Python — Minimal RAG Example</div>
                            <pre><code class="language-python">from langchain_oceanbase import OceanBaseVectorStore
        from langchain_openai import OpenAIEmbeddings, ChatOpenAI
        
        vs = OceanBaseVectorStore(
            embedding=OpenAIEmbeddings(),
            connection_args={"host":"127.0.0.1","port":"2881",
                             "user":"root@test","database":"test"},
        )
        vs.add_texts(["OceanBase is a distributed relational database"])
        print(vs.similarity_search("What is OceanBase?", k=1))</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <aside class="notes">Three steps to run: 1) Docker launch OB 2) pip install 3) Python code. seekdb is lighter, runs on 1C2G.</aside>
                    </section>
        
                    <!-- ══ Slide 10 · Closing ══ -->
                    <section data-background-color="#1a1aff">
                        <div class="slide-hero text-center" style="max-width:860px;">
                            <img src="../assets/logo.png" alt="OceanBase" class="closing-logo" style="height:36px; margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
