                        </div>
                        <div style="margin-top:1.2rem;font-size:0.8rem;color:var(--dim);text-align:center;">
                            <i class="ri-lightbulb-line" style="margin-right:4px;"></i>
                            <strong>seekdb</strong> is OceanBase's AI-native lightweight edition, runs on 1C2G minimum, supports vector and full-text search
                        </div>
                        <aside class="notes">Dify v1.10.1 officially supports MySQL/OceanBase/seekdb as MetaDB and OceanBase as vector store, achieving complete data layer simplification.</aside>
                    </section>
        
                    <!-- ══ Slide 4 · Architecture ══ -->
                    <section data-background-color="#fafafa">
                        <div class="slide-label"><span class="pill">Architecture</span></div>
                        <h2 class="slide-title">Traditional vs seekdb Unified Architecture</h2>
                        <div style="margin-top:1.5rem;text-align:center;">
                            <div style="display:flex;gap:2rem;justify-content:center;align-items:flex-start;">
                                <!-- Traditional Architecture -->
                                <div style="flex:1;max-width:320px;">
                                    <div style="font-size:0.8rem;color:var(--dim);margin-bottom:0.6rem;">Traditional Multi-Component</div>
                                    <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.5rem;">
                                        <div style="background:var(--ob-blue-10);border:1px solid var(--ob-blue);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:0.6rem 1rem;">
                                            <strong style="font-size:0.8rem;">Dify Platform</strong>
                                        </div>
                                        <div style="font-size:1.2rem;color:var(--ghost);">↕ ×3</div>
                                        <div style="display:flex;gap:0.4rem;flex-wrap:wrap;">
                                            <div style="background:#fff3f3;border:1px solid #e88;border-radius:var(--radius);padding:0.5rem 0.6rem;flex:1;min-width:80px;">
                                                <strong style="font-size:0.7rem;color:#c44;">PostgreSQL</strong><br>
                                                <span style="font-size:0.6rem;color:var(--dim);">Metadata</span>
                                            </div>
                                            <div style="background:#fff3f3;border:1px solid #e88;border-radius:var(--radius);padding:0.5rem 0.6rem;flex:1;min-width:80px;">
                                                <strong style="font-size:0.7rem;color:#c44;">Weaviate</strong><br>
                                                <span style="font-size:0.6rem;color:var(--dim);">Vector</span>
                                            </div>
                                            <div style="background:#fff3f3;border:1px solid #e88;border-radius:var(--radius);padding:0.5rem 0.6rem;flex:1;min-width:80px;">
                                                <strong style="font-size:0.7rem;color:#c44;">Elasticsearch</strong><br>
                                                <span style="font-size:0.6rem;color:var(--dim);">Full-Text</span>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <!-- Arrow -->
                                <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;padding-top:2rem;">
                                    <i class="ri-arrow-right-line" style="font-size:2rem;color:var(--ob-teal);"></i>
                                </div>
                                <!-- Unified Architecture -->
                                <div style="flex:1;max-width:320px;">
                                    <div style="font-size:0.8rem;color:var(--dim);margin-bottom:0.6rem;">seekdb Unified Architecture</div>
                                    <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.5rem;">
                                        <div style="background:var(--ob-blue-10);border:1px solid var(--ob-blue);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:0.6rem 1rem;">
                                            <strong style="font-size:0.8rem;">Dify Platform</strong>
                                        </div>
                                        <div style="font-size:1.2rem;color:var(--ghost);">↕ ×1</div>
                                        <div style="background:var(--ob-teal-10);border:2px solid var(--ob-teal);border-radius:var(--radius-lg);padding:0.8rem 1rem;">
                                            <strong style="color:var(--ob-teal);font-size:0.85rem;">OceanBase seekdb</strong><br>
                                            <span style="font-size:0.65rem;color:var(--dim);">Metadata · Vector Index · Full-Text · Hybrid Search</span>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <aside class="notes">Comparison: Traditional architecture requires 3 heterogeneous components vs seekdb unified architecture needs only 1 database.</aside>
                    </section>
        
                    <!-- ══ Slide 5 · Docker Compose ══ -->
                    <section data-background-color="#fafafa">
                        <div class="slide-label"><span class="pill">Deploy</span></div>
                        <h2 class="slide-title">Docker Compose One-Click Deployment</h2>
                        <div class="step-list" style="margin-top:1rem;">
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <span class="step-num">01</span>
                                <div class="step-content">
                                    <strong>Clone Dify Repository</strong>
                                    <p><code>git clone https://github.com/langgenius/dify.git && cd dify/docker</code></p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <span class="step-num">02</span>
                                <div class="step-content">
                                    <strong>Copy Environment Template</strong>
                                    <p><code>cp .env.example .env</code></p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <span class="step-num">03</span>
                                <div class="step-content">
                                    <strong>Configure .env (Recommended Config)</strong>
                                    <p>Set seekdb as both MetaDB and Vector Store</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <span class="step-num">04</span>
                                <div class="step-content">
                                    <strong>Launch Services</strong>
                                    <p><code>docker compose up -d</code> — wait for seekdb Healthy, auto-migration follows</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:1rem;">
                            <div class="code-block-title">.env — seekdb as MetaDB + Vector Store (Recommended)</div>
                            <pre><code class="language-bash"># MetaDB Configuration
        DB_TYPE=mysql
        DB_USERNAME=root
        DB_HOST=seekdb
        DB_PORT=2881
        DB_DATABASE=test
        
        # Vector Store Configuration
        VECTOR_STORE=oceanbase
        OCEANBASE_VECTOR_HOST=seekdb
        OCEANBASE_VECTOR_USER=root
        
        # Launch profile (seekdb only)
        COMPOSE_PROFILES=seekdb</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <aside class="notes">Recommended: seekdb as both MetaDB and Vector Store. COMPOSE_PROFILES=seekdb starts only necessary containers.</aside>
                    </section>
        
                    <!-- ══ Slide 6 · Three Config Options ══ -->
                    <section data-background-color="#fafafa">
                        <div class="slide-label"><span class="pill">Flexible Config</span></div>
                        <h2 class="slide-title">Three Configuration Options</h2>
                        <div class="grid-2" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
                            <div class="callout">
                                <strong><i class="ri-database-line" style="color:var(--ob-blue);margin-right:4px;"></i> Option 1: seekdb as MetaDB Only</strong>
                                <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:0.5rem;font-size:0.75rem;">
                                    <pre><code class="language-bash">DB_TYPE=mysql
        DB_HOST=seekdb
        DB_PORT=2881
        DB_DATABASE=test
        # Vector store uses default</code></pre>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout">
                                <strong><i class="ri-search-line" style="color:var(--ob-teal);margin-right:4px;"></i> Option 2: seekdb as Vector Store Only</strong>
                                <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:0.5rem;font-size:0.75rem;">
                                    <pre><code class="language-bash">VECTOR_STORE=oceanbase
        OCEANBASE_VECTOR_HOST=seekdb
        OCEANBASE_VECTOR_USER=root
        # MetaDB keeps PostgreSQL</code></pre>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="callout" style="margin-top:1rem;border-color:var(--ob-teal);background:var(--ob-teal-10);">
                            <strong><i class="ri-star-line" style="color:var(--ob-teal);margin-right:4px;"></i> Option 3: seekdb as Both MetaDB and Vector Store (Recommended)</strong>
                            <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:0.5rem;font-size:0.75rem;">
                                <pre><code class="language-bash">DB_TYPE=mysql
        DB_HOST=seekdb
        DB_PORT=2881
        DB_DATABASE=test
        VECTOR_STORE=oceanbase
        OCEANBASE_VECTOR_HOST=seekdb
        COMPOSE_PROFILES=seekdb</code></pre>
                            </div>
                            <p style="font-size:0.8rem;margin-top:0.5rem;">One database for everything: metadata + vectors + full-text indexes, zero operational burden</p>
                        </div>
                        <aside class="notes">Three flexible configuration options. Option 3 (unified) is recommended. COMPOSE_PROFILES=seekdb starts only necessary containers.</aside>
                    </section>
        
                    <!-- ══ Slide 7 · Build AI App ══ -->
                    <section data-background-color="#fafafa">
                        <div class="slide-label"><span class="pill">Practice</span></div>
                        <h2 class="slide-title">Build AI Apps with Dify</h2>
                        <div class="step-list" style="margin-top:1rem;">
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <span class="step-num">01</span>
                                <div class="step-content">
                                    <strong>Configure Model Provider</strong>
                                    <p>Settings → Model Provider → Enter API Key (e.g., Alibaba Cloud Bailian) → Select system inference and embedding models</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <span class="step-num">02</span>
                                <div class="step-content">
                                    <strong>Create Knowledge Base</strong>
                                    <p>Knowledge → Create → Index Mode: "High Quality" → Select Embedding Model → Upload documents → Auto chunking and embedding</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <span class="step-num">03</span>
                                <div class="step-content">
                                    <strong>Create ChatBot App</strong>
                                    <p>Studio → Create Blank App → Chat Assistant → Add Knowledge Base context → Debug and preview</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <span class="step-num">04</span>
                                <div class="step-content">
                                    <strong>Publish App</strong>
                                    <p>Click Publish → Run → Get dedicated app page, shareable with your team</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <aside class="notes">Four steps to build an AI app: Configure models → Create knowledge base → Build ChatBot → Publish.</aside>
                    </section>
        
                    <!-- ══ Slide 8 · Verification ══ -->
                    <section data-background-color="#fafafa">
                        <div class="slide-label"><span class="pill">Verification</span></div>
                        <h2 class="slide-title">Deployment Verification & Data Observation</h2>
                        <div class="grid-2" style="margin-top:1.2rem;">
                            <div class="callout">
                                <strong><i class="ri-checkbox-circle-line" style="color:var(--ob-blue);margin-right:4px;"></i> Migration Confirmation</strong>
                                <p>Check api service logs for <code>Database migration successful!</code> to confirm successful migration</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout">
                                <strong><i class="ri-test-tube-line" style="color:var(--ob-teal);margin-right:4px;"></i> Vector Capability Test</strong>
                                <p>Create knowledge base → Upload documents → Observe chunks and indexes → Successful embedding and retrieval confirms configuration</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout">
                                <strong><i class="ri-terminal-line" style="color:var(--ob-blue);margin-right:4px;"></i> SQL Direct Connection</strong>
                                <p><code>mysql -h127.0.0.1 -P2881 -uroot -Dtest</code> to view knowledge base schema and vector data</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout">
                                <strong><i class="ri-bar-chart-line" style="color:var(--ob-teal);margin-right:4px;"></i> Resource Usage</strong>
                                <p>seekdb container memory stable at ~1GB, runs on 1C2G, handles both relational and vector workloads</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:1rem;">
                            <div class="code-block-title">Verify Migration Status & Connect to Database</div>
                            <pre><code class="language-bash"># Check api service logs
        docker logs -f docker-api-1
        
        # Success indicator
        # ✅ Database migration successful!
        
        # SQL direct connection to seekdb
        mysql -h127.0.0.1 -P2881 -uroot@test -p
        
        # View databases
        SHOW DATABASES;
        
        # Switch to dify database
        USE dify;
        
        # View tables
        SHOW TABLES;
        
        # View knowledge base schema
        DESC vector_index_xxx_node;</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <aside class="notes">Confirm successful migration via logs, observe knowledge base data structure via SQL direct connection to verify vector store configuration.</aside>
                    </section>
        
                    <!-- ══ Slide 9 · Closing ══ -->
                    <section data-background-color="#1a1aff">
                        <div class="slide-hero text-center" style="max-width:860px;">
                            <h2 style="color:#fff;font-size:2rem;">Dify + seekdb: One Database for Agentic RAG</h2>
                            <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.85);margin-top:0.8rem;font-size:0.9rem;">Unified Storage · Native Hybrid Search · Transactional Consistency · Minimal Operations</p>
                            <div style="margin-top:2rem;display:flex;gap:1.5rem;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap;">
