                        <h2 class="slide-title">PowerRAG Technical Architecture</h2>
                        <div style="margin-top:1.5rem;text-align:center;">
                            <div style="display:inline-flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.6rem;max-width:720px;">
                                <div style="background:var(--ob-blue-10);border:2px solid var(--ob-blue);border-radius:var(--radius-lg);padding:0.8rem 2rem;">
                                    <strong style="color:var(--ob-blue);">PowerRAG Extension Layer</strong><br>
                                    <span style="font-size:0.72rem;color:var(--dim);">Enterprise Enhancements · Knowledge Governance · Memory Management · Agent Chat · Multi-Tenant</span>
                                </div>
                                <div style="font-size:1.2rem;color:var(--ghost);">↕</div>
                                <div style="background:#f0f0ff;border:2px solid #6366f1;border-radius:var(--radius-lg);padding:0.8rem 2rem;">
                                    <strong style="color:#6366f1;">RAGFlow Core Framework</strong><br>
                                    <span style="font-size:0.72rem;color:var(--dim);">Document Parsing · Chunking · Vector Embedding · Retrieval Engine · Agent Flow</span>
                                </div>
                                <div style="font-size:1.2rem;color:var(--ghost);">↕</div>
                                <div style="background:var(--ob-teal-10);border:2px solid var(--ob-teal);border-radius:var(--radius-lg);padding:0.8rem 2rem;">
                                    <strong style="color:var(--ob-teal);">OceanBase Multi-Modal Database</strong><br>
                                    <span style="font-size:0.72rem;color:var(--dim);">Metadata (OLTP) · Vector Index (HNSW) · Full-Text (FULLTEXT) · JSON · GIS</span>
                                </div>
                                <div style="font-size:1.2rem;color:var(--ghost);">↕</div>
                                <div style="display:flex;gap:0.6rem;justify-content:center;">
                                    <div style="background:var(--lift);border:1px solid var(--rule);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:0.6rem 1rem;flex:1;">
                                        <strong style="font-size:0.8rem;">Redis</strong><br>
                                        <span style="font-size:0.65rem;color:var(--dim);">Cache & Queue</span>
                                    </div>
                                    <div style="background:var(--lift);border:1px solid var(--rule);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:0.6rem 1rem;flex:1;">
                                        <strong style="font-size:0.8rem;">MinIO</strong><br>
                                        <span style="font-size:0.65rem;color:var(--dim);">Object Storage</span>
                                    </div>
                                    <div style="background:var(--lift);border:1px solid var(--rule);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:0.6rem 1rem;flex:1;">
                                        <strong style="font-size:0.8rem;">Elasticsearch</strong><br>
                                        <span style="font-size:0.65rem;color:var(--dim);">Full-Text (Optional)</span>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <aside class="notes">Three-layer architecture: PowerRAG Extension → RAGFlow Core → OceanBase Foundation. OB replaces MySQL as primary DB.</aside>
                    </section>
        
                    <!-- ══ Slide 5 · Key Features ══ -->
                    <section data-background-color="#fafafa">
                        <div class="slide-label"><span class="pill">Features</span></div>
                        <h2 class="slide-title">PowerRAG Key Capabilities</h2>
                        <div class="grid-2" style="margin-top:1.2rem;">
                            <div class="callout">
                                <strong><i class="ri-brain-line" style="color:var(--ob-blue);margin-right:4px;"></i> Memory Management</strong>
                                <p>Observable Agent memory extraction, embedding, and storage. RESTful API + Python SDK for CRUD and intelligent retrieval.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout">
                                <strong><i class="ri-chat-3-line" style="color:var(--ob-teal);margin-right:4px;"></i> Agent Chat</strong>
                                <p>Built-in Agent chat interface with full conversation history preservation and multi-session management.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout">
                                <strong><i class="ri-folder-shield-line" style="color:var(--ob-blue);margin-right:4px;"></i> Knowledge Governance</strong>
                                <p>Batch metadata management, file status tracking, quality monitoring — governable data assets.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout">
                                <strong><i class="ri-user-settings-line" style="color:var(--ob-teal);margin-right:4px;"></i> Multi-Admin Support</strong>
                                <p>Breaks single-admin limitation. Multiple superuser roles for enterprise org structures.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <aside class="notes">PowerRAG adds Memory, Agent Chat, Knowledge Governance, and Multi-Admin on top of RAGFlow.</aside>
                    </section>
        
                    <!-- ══ Slide 6 · OceanBase as RAGFlow DB ══ -->
                    <section data-background-color="#fafafa">
                        <div class="slide-label"><span class="pill">OB Replacement</span></div>
                        <h2 class="slide-title">OceanBase Replaces MySQL — Advantages</h2>
                        <table style="margin-top:1rem;">
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th style="width:25%;">Dimension</th>
                                    <th style="width:37%;">MySQL + External Vector DB</th>
                                    <th style="width:38%;background:var(--ob-blue-10);">OceanBase Unified Engine</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><strong>Metadata</strong></td>
                                    <td>MySQL</td>
                                    <td style="background:var(--ob-blue-10);">OceanBase (MySQL compatible)</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><strong>Vector Search</strong></td>
                                    <td>Requires Pinecone / Weaviate</td>
                                    <td style="background:var(--ob-blue-10);"><strong>Built-in HNSW vector index</strong></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><strong>Full-Text</strong></td>
                                    <td>Requires Elasticsearch</td>
                                    <td style="background:var(--ob-blue-10);"><strong>Built-in FULLTEXT index</strong></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><strong>Consistency</strong></td>
                                    <td>Cross-system sync with lag</td>
                                    <td style="background:var(--ob-blue-10);"><strong>ACID transactions, zero lag</strong></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><strong>Ops Complexity</strong></td>
                                    <td>3+ systems to manage</td>
                                    <td style="background:var(--ob-blue-10);"><strong>1 engine</strong></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><strong>Migration Cost</strong></td>
                                    <td>—</td>
                                    <td style="background:var(--ob-blue-10);"><strong>MySQL protocol compatible, zero rewrite</strong></td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                        <aside class="notes">OceanBase replaces MySQL + Vector DB + ES trio. MySQL protocol compatible, zero-rewrite migration.</aside>
                    </section>
        
                    <!-- ══ Slide 7 · Memory System ══ -->
                    <section data-background-color="#fafafa">
                        <div class="slide-label"><span class="pill">Memory</span></div>
                        <h2 class="slide-title">Agent Memory System — PowerMem</h2>
                        <div class="step-list" style="margin-top:1rem;">
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <span class="step-num">01</span>
                                <div class="step-content">
                                    <strong>Memory Extraction</strong>
                                    <p>Auto-extract key info from conversations, async embedding & storage, full log traceability</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <span class="step-num">02</span>
                                <div class="step-content">
                                    <strong>Persistent Storage</strong>
                                    <p>OceanBase vector storage with ACID guarantees — memories never lost, cross-session persistence</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <span class="step-num">03</span>
                                <div class="step-content">
                                    <strong>Intelligent Retrieval</strong>
                                    <p>Keyword + semantic similarity dual-path retrieval for fast memory lookup</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step-item">
                                <span class="step-num">04</span>
                                <div class="step-content">
                                    <strong>API Integration</strong>
                                    <p>RESTful API + Python SDK for CRUD, enable/disable, and forgetting management</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div style="margin-top:1rem;background:var(--ob-blue-10);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:1rem 1.2rem;">
                            <strong style="color:var(--ob-blue);font-size:0.85rem;"><i class="ri-trophy-line" style="margin-right:4px;"></i> LOCOMO Benchmark SOTA</strong>
                            <p style="font-size:0.78rem;color:var(--dim);margin-top:4px;">PowerMem achieves SOTA on the LOCOMO long-term memory benchmark while slashing context token usage by 96%.</p>
                        </div>
                        <aside class="notes">PowerMem is an Agent memory system built on seekdb. SOTA on LOCOMO benchmark, 96% token reduction.</aside>
                    </section>
        
                    <!-- ══ Slide 8 · Enterprise RAG ══ -->
                    <section data-background-color="#fafafa">
                        <div class="slide-label"><span class="pill">Enterprise</span></div>
                        <h2 class="slide-title">Enterprise RAG Best Practices</h2>
                        <div class="grid-2" style="margin-top:1.2rem;">
                            <div class="callout">
                                <strong><i class="ri-shield-check-line" style="color:var(--ob-blue);margin-right:4px;"></i> Data Security</strong>
                                <p>OceanBase encryption in transit + TDE, knowledge base access control, multi-tenant isolation</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout">
                                <strong><i class="ri-bar-chart-box-line" style="color:var(--ob-teal);margin-right:4px;"></i> Observability</strong>
                                <p>Memory extraction status & logs, retrieval quality monitoring, token usage statistics</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout">
                                <strong><i class="ri-scale-line" style="color:var(--ob-blue);margin-right:4px;"></i> High Availability</strong>
                                <p>OceanBase Paxos protocol, RPO=0, RTO<30s, 7×24 business continuity</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout">
                                <strong><i class="ri-expand-diagonal-line" style="color:var(--ob-teal);margin-right:4px;"></i> Elastic Scaling</strong>
                                <p>Online scale-out/in, knowledge base from GB to TB without downtime</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <aside class="notes">Enterprise RAG focuses on data security, observability, high availability, and elastic scaling. OceanBase has natural advantages.</aside>
                    </section>
        
                    <!-- ══ Slide 9 · Quick Start ══ -->
                    <section data-background-color="#fafafa">
                        <div class="slide-label"><span class="pill">Quick Start</span></div>
                        <h2 class="slide-title">Deploy PowerRAG in 5 Minutes</h2>
                        <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:1rem;">
                            <div class="code-block-title">Shell — Docker Compose Launch</div>
                            <pre><code class="language-bash"># Clone PowerRAG repository
        git clone https://github.com/oceanbase/powerrag.git
        cd powerrag
        
        # Docker Compose launch (built-in OceanBase)
        docker compose up -d
        
        # Or pull directly from Docker Hub
        docker pull oceanbase/powerrag:latest</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:0.6rem;">
                            <div class="code-block-title">Configure LLM Models</div>
                            <pre><code class="language-yaml"># Configure models in PowerRAG console
        # Settings → Model Providers → Add Ollama / OpenAI / vLLM
        
        # Recommended: Ollama local deployment
        ollama pull llama3.2    # Chat model
        ollama pull bge-m3      # Embedding model
        
        # PowerRAG Settings
        Chat Model: llama3.2
        Embedding Model: bge-m3
        Base URL: http://host.docker.internal:11434</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:0.6rem;">
                            <div class="code-block-title">Create Knowledge Base & Start Chat</div>
                            <pre><code class="text">1. Knowledge Base → New → Upload documents (PDF/Markdown/Excel)
        2. Select chunking strategy → Auto parse & embed
        3. Chat → Link knowledge base → Start RAG conversation
        4. Agent → Create Agent Flow → Add Memory node</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <aside class="notes">Three steps: 1) Docker launch 2) Configure LLM models 3) Create knowledge base and start chatting. Supports Ollama local models.</aside>
                    </section>
        
